---
description: Spacing uses Tailwind default scale only
globs: "**/*.{ts,tsx,css,scss}"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Spacing Rules

- Use Tailwind default spacing scale utilities (examples: `p-4`, `mt-2`, `gap-3`).
- Avoid arbitrary values (examples: `p-[13px]`, `m-[5.5px]`).
- Do NOT create a custom spacing token system or custom spacing keys.
- Prefer existing spacing values already used elsewhere in the UI.

# CSS/SCSS Notes

- If you must write spacing outside Tailwind, avoid one-off random values (hex/px-like spacing).
- Keep new values aligned to the same “default scale” intent you use with Tailwind utilities.

